ZH: 1. 我指着地图上的那个标记所指的地方。
EN: 1. I pointed to the spot indicated by the marker on the map.
ZH: 2. 这个符号所指的意思是停车场。
EN: 2. The symbol indicates a parking lot.
ZH: 3. 我们需要明确所指的时间段。
EN: 3. We need to specify the time period being referred to.
ZH: 4. 在这个问题上，他的观点并不是很清楚所指。
EN: 4. His viewpoint is not very clear on this issue.
ZH: 5. 对于这个词的含义，不同的人可能有不同所指。
EN: 5. Different people may have different referents for this word.
ZH: 6. 他的回答让我对他所指的事情感到迷惑。
EN: 6. His answer left me confused about what he was referring to.
ZH: 7. 我想确认我理解你所指的目标。
EN: 7. I would like to confirm that I understand the goal you are referring to.
ZH: 8. 为了避免歧义，我们需要明确所指的主题。
EN: 8. To avoid ambiguity, we need to specify the topic being referred to.
ZH: 9. 这本书中的“它”所指的是一只狗。
EN: 9. The "it" in this book refers to a dog.
ZH: 10. 他用手指所指的地方是我们的下一站。
EN: 10. The place he pointed to with his finger is our next stop.
ZH: 11. 他能准确地描述出自己所指的对象。
EN: 11. He can accurately describe the object he is referring to.
ZH: 12. 这个单词的意义很依赖于上下文中所指的内容。
EN: 12. The meaning of this word heavily relies on the content being referred to in the context.
ZH: 13. 这个词所指的东西是不可见的。
EN: 13. The thing referred to by this word is invisible.
ZH: 14. 请详细说明你所指的这个概念。
EN: 14. Please provide a detailed explanation of the concept you are referring to.
ZH: 15. 我们将讨论复杂系统中所指的关键组件。
EN: 15. We will discuss the key components being referred to in complex systems.
ZH: 16. 所指的问题在我们的报告中得到了详细解释。
EN: 16. The issues being referred to have been explained in detail in our report.
ZH: 17. 现在是时候澄清你所指的模型了。
EN: 17. It is time to clarify the model you are referring to.
ZH: 18. 我们需要确定作者对于“善良”所指的具体含义。
EN: 18. We need to determine the specific meaning the author refers to with "kindness."
ZH: 19. 这个词常常具有多重所指的含义。
EN: 19. This word often has multiple referents.
ZH: 20. 你可以给出一些例子来说明你所指的这个概念吗？
EN: 20. Can you provide some examples to illustrate the concept you are referring to?
